# Auto-dev mode (ecosystem fleet)

**SoR:** `bridge-os/pm/auto-dev-mode.json` · **Wave batches:** `bridge-os/pm/spec/execution-wave-batches.json`

## Default mode: `complete_milestones`

Sprint ceremony repo — execution stop logic is **bridge SoR**. Agents in owner repos follow continuous mode rules via bridge P22.

| Mode | Stop when |
|------|-----------|
| `complete_sprint` | Current sprint done |
| `complete_all_sprints` | All program sprints done |
| `complete_roadmap` | `roadmapExecutionComplete` |
| `complete_milestones` | `milestoneExecutionComplete` (**default**) |

## One exit predicate

See `bridge-os/.cursor/rules/agent-auto-dev-mode.mdc` — deny-list + `mayCloseTurn` from `pnpm --dir ../bridge-os ecosystem:turn-exit:check --write`.

## Wave batch

Status Update milestone = batch ID (`W4-docs-IA`), not per-repo seal. Manifest: `bridge-os/pm/spec/execution-wave-batches.json`.

## Guards

- Never **stop after a single story** in continuous auto-dev mode.
- Never **ask which story is next** — P22 delegated to bridge-os selects the next work item.
- Never emit a status update **without** a **progress** block.
